 Police are investigating a case of business robbery after two men, armed with knives, stormed into a clothing store and stole several clothing items in KwaNobuhle on Wednesday. "On Wednesday, at around 15:00, two men stormed into a clothing store situated at the KwaNobuhle Shopping Mall, Matanzima Road, KwaNobuhle," described police spokesperson,  Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "It is alleged that the two men grabbed clothes from the rails and when accosted by security and staff, both men drew knives and ran out of the store with the stolen items." Anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of the suspects is urged to contact the nearest police station or Crime Stop on 08600 10111. 